body:
Thinking more about this, I think it is much safer to treat `@immutable` as a meta-interface that applies to everything, without restrictions. Applying `@immutable` to an interface should propagate `@immutable` at class level to all implementations.

As an example:

```php
<?php
  
  
/** @psalm-immutable */
interface Money
{
     public function gimme() : int;
}

final class MyMoney implements Money
{
    private int $amount = 0;
    public function gimme() : int
    {
        return $this->amount;
    }
    public function increment() : void
    {
        $this->amount += 1;
    }
}

/** @psalm-immutable */
class MyBankAccount
{
     private Money $money; // problem: my bank account is now mutable
     public function __construct(Money $money) { $this->money = $money; }
}
```

